---
openapi: 3.0.2
info:
  description: "Apigee Data API demonstration."
  version: 1.0.0
  title: Apigee Data API
servers:
  - url: https://$APIGEE_X_HOSTNAME/london/bikes/v1
paths:
  /:
    get:
      summary: View Bike Rentals
      description: Let's you access data from the public BigQuery dataset on bike rentals in London.
      parameters:
        - name: limit
          in: query
          description: Max number of returned results.
          required: false
          schema:
            type: number
        - name: offset
          in: query
          description: Pagination Offset.
          required: false
          schema:
            type: number
        - name: fields
          in: query
          description: List of fields separated by comma.
          required: false
          schema:
            type: string
        - name: x-apikey
          in: header
          description: API key for identifying the request.
          required: false
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful operation
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                type: array
                items:
                  $ref: "#/components/schemas/BikeRental"
components:
  schemas:
    BikeRental:
      type: object
      properties:
        rental_id:
          type: string
          example: "12345"
        duration:
          type: string
          description: "rental duration in seconds"
          example: "600"
        bike_id:
          type: string
          example: "7000"
        end_station_id:
          type: string
          example: "42"
        end_date:
          type: string
          example: "1.4412843E9"
        end_station_name:
          type: string
          example: "Station Name X"
        end_station_logical_terminal:
          type: string
          example: "1111"
        end_station_priority_id:
          type: string
          example: "456"
        start_station_id:
          type: string
          example: "43"
        start_date:
          type: string
          example: "1.4412843E9"
        start_station_name:
          type: string
          example: "Station Name Y"
        start_station_logical_terminal:
          type: string
          example: "1111"
